name: Authentication
description: The Authentication APIs provide a convenient way to convert classic authentication responses into entity authentication models. These APIs will provide you with the entity authentication token needed for subsequent Entity API calls. Manage API keys for authenticating any entity.

properties.name: APIKeySecret
properties.description: Secret used to authenticate requests with the key. Set in the "X - EntityAPIKeyId" in authentication requests.The secret value is returned only once in this response and cannot be retrieved afterward, either via API or in Game Manager.API key secrets should be stored securely only on trusted servers and never distributed in code or configuration to untrusted clients.

GetEntityTokenRequest.name: GetEntityTokenRequest
GetEntityTokenRequest.description: This API must be called with X-SecretKey, X-Authentication or X-EntityToken headers. An optional EntityKey may be included to attempt to set the resulting EntityToken to a specific entity, however the entity must be a relation of the caller, such as the master_player_account of a character. If sending X-EntityToken the account will be marked as freshly logged in and will issue a new token. If using X-Authentication or X-EntityToken the header must still be valid and cannot be expired or revoked.

calls.name: ActivateKey
calls.summary: Activates the given API key. Active keys may be used for authentication.

calls.name: CreateKey
calls.summary: Creates an API key for the given entity.

calls.name: DeactivateKey
calls.summary: Deactivates the given API key, causing subsequent authentication attempts with it to fail.Deactivating a key is a way to verify that the key is not in use before deleting it.

calls.name: GetEntityToken
calls.summary: Method to exchange a legacy AuthenticationTicket or title SecretKey for an Entity Token or to refresh a still valid Entity Token.
calls.requestDetails: This API must be called with X-SecretKey, X-Authentication or X-EntityToken headers. An optional EntityKey may be included to attempt to set the resulting EntityToken to a specific entity, however the entity must be a relation of the caller, such as the master_player_account of a character. If sending X-EntityToken the account will be marked as freshly logged in and will issue a new token. If using X-Authentication or X-EntityToken the header must still be valid and cannot be expired or revoked.

calls.name: GetKeys
calls.summary: Gets the API keys associated with the given entity.

calls.name: ValidateEntityToken
calls.summary: Method for a server to validate a client provided EntityToken. Only callable by the title entity.
calls.requestDetails: Given an entity token, validates that it hasn't exipired or been revoked and will return details of the owner.
